org.apache.flex.compiler.projects

Interface IFlexProject

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IASProject, ICompilerProject, IWriteOnlyProjectSettings, IXMLNameResolver
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FlexJSProject, FlexProject

    public interface IFlexProject
extends IASProject, IXMLNameResolver, IWriteOnlyProjectSettings
    Base interface for all project types that support all flex source file types ( mxml, fxg, css, etc ).

      • setLocaleDependentResources

        void setLocaleDependentResources(Map<String,String> localeDependentResources)
        Sets the locale dependent path map for the project. For each entry, the key is the path of a locale dependent resource (source path or library path entry) and the value is the locale it depends on.
        Parameters:
        localeDependentResources - map that contains project's locale dependent resources

      • getResourceLocale

        String getResourceLocale(String path)
        Returns the locale of the resource with a given path if the resource is locale dependent. This currently returns the locale for only source path and library path entries, which are the only resources passed to compiler and can contain {locale} token.
        Parameters:
        path - path of a file/directory for which to determine the locale
        Returns:
        locale of the resource with a given path if the resource is locale dependent or null if the resource is not locale dependent.

      • setRuntimeSharedLibraryPath

        void setRuntimeSharedLibraryPath(List<RSLSettings> rsls)
        Set the RSL library path with an ordered list of RSLs. The runtime will load the RSLs in the order specified.
        Parameters:
        rsls - Each RSLSettings in the list describes an RSL and its failovers. If null, the list of RSLs is reset.

      • computeLibraryDependencies

        Set<String> computeLibraryDependencies(File targetLibrary,
                                     DependencyTypeSet dependencyTypeSet)
                                       throws LibraryCircularDependencyException
        Get the set of libraries a given library depends on.
        Parameters:
        targetLibrary - The library to find dependencies for. May not be null.
        dependencyTypeSet - The types of dependencies to consider when determining the library's dependencies. If this parameter is null or an empty set, then all dependencies will be considered.
        Returns:
        A set of Strings; where each String is the location of a library in the file system.
        Throws:
        LibraryCircularDependencyException

      • computeLibraryDependencyOrder

        List<String> computeLibraryDependencyOrder(DependencyTypeSet dependencySet)
                                           throws LibraryCircularDependencyException
        Get the dependency order of libraries on the internal library path and external library path of this project.
        Parameters:
        dependencySet - The types of dependencies to consider when determining the dependency order. If this parameter is null or an empty set, then all dependencies will be considered.
        Returns:
        An ordered list of library dependencies. Each String in the list is the location of a library in the file system. The first library in the list has no dependencies. Each library in the list has at least the same dependencies as its predecessor and may be dependent on its predecessor as well.
        Throws:
        LibraryCircularDependencyException

      • getThemeNames

        List<String> getThemeNames()
        Get the names of all the themes used in this project.
        Returns:
        A list of theme names.

      • isFlex

        boolean isFlex()
        Option of enable or prevent various Flex compiler behaviors. This is currently used to enable/disable the generation of a root class for library swfs and generation of code for application swfs.

      • getTagNamesForClass

        Collection<XMLName> getTagNamesForClass(String className)
        Uses the manifest information to find all the MXML tags that map to a specified fully-qualified ActionScript classname, such as as "spark.controls.Button"
        Parameters:
        className - Fully-qualified ActionScript classname, such as as "spark.controls.Button"
        Returns:
        A collection of XMLName's representing a MXML tags, such as a "Button" tag in the namespace "library://ns.adobe.com/flex/spark".
